⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Doyle
node INT · INT · ⟦Doyle:INT:820e88⟧

WHO   — Doyle — lost on Miller's planet
WHAT  — The first of the away team to die — caught by a tidal wave hundreds of feet high on the water world, lost while the others barely escape.
WHERE — INT · Interstellar  Framework inputs: Interstellar (2014, dir. Christopher Nolan)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film needs the indifferent scale of the cosmos to take someone competent and blameless, to make the stakes real.
HOW   — By the bad luck of the wave and the cruel clock of a planet where every minute costs years above.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I did everything right — and a wave the size of a mountain took me anyway, because the cosmos does not care that I tried.

